(N'DISABLE_VERSIONING',N'OTHER_OR_NEW',2,0,N'Occurs when SQL Server polls the version transaction manager to see whether the timestamp of the earliest active transaction is later than the timestamp of when the state started changing. If this is this case, all the snapshot transactions that were star',N'Spezialisierter, interner oder neuer SQL-Server-Wait-Type.',N'Hohe Werte sind nur im Delta- und Workload-Kontext bewertbar.',N'Aktive Tasks, Ressource, Version, SQLskills-Detailseite und Herstellerdokumentation prüfen.',N'REFERENCE_NORMALIZED',N'IMPORTED_REVIEW_REQUIRED'),
(N'DISKIO_SUSPEND',N'STORAGE_DATA_IO',2,0,N'Occurs when a task is waiting to access a file when an external backup is active. This is reported for each waiting user process. A count larger than five per user process may indicate that the external backup is taking too much time to finish.',N'Daten-, Metadaten- oder asynchroner Datei-I/O.',N'Hohe Delta-Werte können auf Storage-Latenz, Scans oder Buffer-Pool-Druck hinweisen.',N'sys.dm_io_virtual_file_stats, Volume, Buffer Pool, große Reads und aktive Operation korrelieren.',N'REFERENCE_NORMALIZED',N'IMPORTED_REVIEW_REQUIRED'),
